# Frontend Rules — aide

## Component Design

- Presentational components receive data via props
- Container components handle data fetching and state
- One component per file; co-locate styles when applicable

## State Management

- Prefer local state; lift only when shared
- Server state via dedicated data layer — no ad-hoc fetch in leaf components
- Avoid prop drilling beyond two levels — use context or store

## UX Requirements

- Loading, empty, and error states for every async view
- Accessible: semantic HTML, ARIA where needed, keyboard navigation
- Responsive layouts for mobile and desktop breakpoints

## Performance

- Lazy-load routes and heavy components
- Memoize expensive computations
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders

## Reference

- Product scope: `docs/project.md`
- Standards: `docs/coding-standards.md`

## Prohibited

- Business logic duplication that belongs in domain layer
- Inline secrets or API keys
- `any` types in component props
